{
  "id": "RAW_c9f4dd",
  "title": "AI 界面设计模式：来自 Smashing 杂志",
  "url": "https://smashingmagazine.com/2025/07/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/",
  "date": "2025-07-14 15:00:00",
  "author": "hello@smashingmagazine.com (Vitaly Friedman)",
  "siteName": "Smashing Magazine",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div class=\"c-garfield-the-cat\">\n   <div class=\"c-garfield-summary\">\n    <section aria-label=\"Quick summary\" class=\"article__summary\">\n     Designing a new AI feature? Where do you even begin? Here’s a simple, practical overview with useful design patterns for better AI experiences. More design patterns in <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/\">Smart Interface Design Patterns</a>, a <strong>friendly video course on UX</strong> and design patterns by Vitaly — from complex data tables and nested filters to FAQs and error messages.\n    </section>\n   </div>\n   <p>So you need to <strong>design a new AI feature</strong> for your product. How would you start? How do you design flows and interactions? And how do you ensure that that new feature doesn’t get abandoned by users after a few runs?</p>\n   <p>In this article, I’d love to share <strong>a very simple but systematic approach</strong> to how I think about designing AI experiences. Hopefully, it will help you get a bit more clarity about how to get started.</p>\n   <p class=\"course-intro\">This article is <strong>part of our ongoing series</strong> on <a href=\"https://smashingmagazine.com/category/ux\">UX</a>. You can find more details on <strong>design patterns and UX strategy</strong> in <a style=\"font-weight:700\" href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/\">Smart Interface Design Patterns</a>&nbsp;🍣 — with live UX training coming up soon. <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com\">Jump to table of contents</a>.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"the-receding-role-of-ai-chat\">The Receding Role of AI Chat</h2>\n   <p>One of the key recent shifts is a slow move away from traditional <strong>“chat-alike” AI interfaces</strong>. As Luke Wroblewski <a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2105\">wrote</a>, when agents can use multiple tools, call other agents and run in the background, users <em>orchestrate</em> AI work more — there’s a lot less chatting back and forth.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2105\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"610\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/14055efa-0e24-4b44-1d4e-cecc3dfe3200/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/658b1101-9e58-4a1c-178e-4a5db4987200/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e3d38a5e-4acf-47f0-c234-be69612e2e00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/11983709-deae-40d9-3327-cfd13a5b2300/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bdb09bb7-ca00-48bf-4e40-d5a81a35b300/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/14055efa-0e24-4b44-1d4e-cecc3dfe3200/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"AI Experience Paradigm by Luke Wroblewski\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Messaging UI <a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2105\">slowly starts feeling dated</a>, and chat UI fades into background. By Luke Wroblewski. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/1-ai-experience-paradigm.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>In fact, chatbots are <strong>rarely a great experience paradigm</strong> — mostly because the burden of articulating intent efficiently lies on the user. But in practice, it’s remarkably difficult to do well and very time-consuming.</p>\n   <p>Chat doesn’t go away, of course, but it’s being complemented with <strong>task-oriented UIs</strong> — temperature controls, knobs, sliders, buttons, semantic spreadsheets, infinite canvases — with AI providing predefined options, presets, and templates.</p>\n   <figure>\n    <a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2106\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"707\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/690a8a31-411b-4046-845e-b3d57e1bf000/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f46e50b5-b863-41fd-6d8a-bda945ae1c00/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5b1c3d00-b979-4e59-b09e-d708b41a4200/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3091619a-78ea-4298-82b1-4d266b7ce600/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b8cf5f2d-1049-4c62-ad67-80e35fd80100/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/690a8a31-411b-4046-845e-b3d57e1bf000/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"AI Experience Paradigm by Luke Wroblewski\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     <a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2106\">Agentic AI design patterns</a>, with more task-oriented UIs, rather than chat. By Luke Wroblewski. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/2-agentic-ai-design-patterns.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>There, AI emphasizes the work, the plan, the tasks — the outcome, instead of the chat input. The results are experiences that truly <strong>amplify value for users</strong> by sprinkling a bit of AI in places where it delivers real value to real users.</p>\n   <p>To design better AI experiences, we need to study <strong>5 key areas</strong> that we need to shape.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"input-ux-expressing-intent\">Input UX: Expressing Intent</h2>\n   <p><strong>Conversational AI</strong> is a <strong>very slow</strong> way of helping users express and articulate their intent. Usability tests <a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/accordion-editing-apple-picking/\">show</a> that users often get lost in editing, reviewing, typing, and re-typing. It’s painfully slow, often taking 30-60 seconds for input.</p>\n   <p>As it turns out, people have a hard time expressing their intent well. In fact, instead of writing prompts manually, it’s a good idea to <a href=\"https://spectrum.ieee.org/prompt-engineering-is-dead\">ask AI to write a prompt</a> to feed itself.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.florafauna.ai/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"439\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1896091b-c4a4-4846-a351-dbf23cd4f700/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/75e1b05a-25c4-4987-f45d-bbe9bc152500/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5ed49218-2297-4b5a-5b25-74d3764d4300/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b0daf289-245d-42c5-05d0-bf5df1479700/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b95adeb8-4e49-4916-bc60-70cbf903a500/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1896091b-c4a4-4846-a351-dbf23cd4f700/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration: How users can express their intent in AI interfaces.\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     <a href=\"https://www.florafauna.ai/\">Flora AI</a> allows you to modify images and videos via nodes. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/3-flora-ai.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>With <a href=\"https://www.florafauna.ai/\">Flora AI</a>, users can still write prompts, but they <strong>visualize their intent</strong> with nodes by connecting various sources visually. Instead of elaborately explaining to AI how we need the pipeline to work, we attach nodes and commands on a canvas.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.krea.ai/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"380\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2fab4e38-8ace-41f0-982b-3443acc2c900/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dbe427f4-2f38-4b7d-8f6a-19af6fe90300/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9e1ecfd2-cd20-4c24-74ea-f85d8c722b00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/914a0328-b729-41b9-10fd-ce085a823800/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6ffd8f80-9c57-48d7-ddca-3988362ec000/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2fab4e38-8ace-41f0-982b-3443acc2c900/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     With <a href=\"https://www.krea.ai/\">Krea.ai</a>, users can move abstract shapes (on the left) to explain their goal to AI and study the outcome (on the right). (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/4-illustration-output-ux.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>With input for AI, being precise is slow and challenging. Instead, we can <strong>abstract away</strong> the object we want to manipulate, and give AI precise input by moving that abstracted object on a canvas. That’s what <a href=\"https://www.krea.ai/\">Krea.ai</a> does.</p>\n   <p>In summary, we can <strong>minimize the burden of typing</strong> prompts manually — with AI-generated pre-prompts, prompt extensions, query builders, and also voice input.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"output-ux-displaying-outcomes\">Output UX: Displaying Outcomes</h2>\n   <p>AI output doesn’t have to be merely plain text or a list of bullet points. It must be <strong>helpful to drive people to insights</strong>, faster. For example, we could visualize output by creating additional explanations based on the user’s goal and motivations.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/5-illustration-output-ux.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4b0978d1-5c87-4334-7a30-8ebea5e52e00/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e4128d20-9a22-4232-5472-65b9b3646300/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a42cfe42-e59c-4423-8ecd-a2a5c5c4fc00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5ef0bee2-05b6-44f1-78b6-bac0b7eee600/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/90a71902-ea67-4856-f833-e4a3e8033000/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4b0978d1-5c87-4334-7a30-8ebea5e52e00/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Visualizing outcome through style lenses. By Amelia Wattenberger. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/5-illustration-output-ux.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>For example, Amelia Wattenberger <a href=\"https://wattenberger.com/thoughts/boo-chatbots\">visualized AI output</a> for her text editor PenPal by adding <strong>style lenses</strong> to explore the content from. The output could be visualized in sentence lengths and scales <em>Sad — Happy</em>, <em>Concrete — Abstract</em>, and so on.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.aino.world/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"545\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ba7a20f7-52c0-4763-8fc1-908eb8ecc000/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/139cb99b-9c88-4810-0dd5-a95fc06b0e00/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/505032f1-f693-4a70-1a11-c877e942f600/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0de82622-fd0b-4faa-5129-27e02918ea00/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/71ca0609-8717-4c17-690f-b184bd80d200/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ba7a20f7-52c0-4763-8fc1-908eb8ecc000/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     <a href=\"https://www.aino.world/\">Aino.ai</a>, an AI GIS Analyst for urban planning. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/6-aino-ai.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>The outcome could also be visualized on a map, which, of course, is expected for an <a href=\"https://www.aino.world/\">AI GIS analyst</a>. Also, users can <strong>access individual data layers</strong>, turn them on and off, and hence explore the data on the map.</p>\n   <p>We can also use <a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/accordion-editing-apple-picking/\">forced ranking</a> and prioritizations to <strong>suggest best options</strong> and avoid choice paralysis — even if a user asks for top 10 recommendations. We can think about ways to present results as a data table, or a dashboard, or a visualization on a map, or as a structured JSON file, for example.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"refinement-ux-tweaking-output\">Refinement UX: Tweaking Output</h2>\n   <p>Users often need to <a href=\"https://www.nngroup.com/articles/accordion-editing-apple-picking/\">cherry-pick</a> some bits from the AI output and bring them together in a new place — and often they need to <strong>expand on one section</strong>, synthesize bits from another section, or just refine the outcome to meet their needs.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.adobe.com/products/firefly.html\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/08c2f50a-9622-4d19-dc61-d917a219b600/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a60fa455-5627-436e-6ed4-b7b7f7511000/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/cc934a96-47a1-477f-e6b0-12d3fadad800/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ea6d6575-2a29-4bc7-0010-a4505a7ddc00/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/13ad2ecc-2f1a-4bf2-80d1-56c75e444500/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/08c2f50a-9622-4d19-dc61-d917a219b600/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     <a href=\"https://www.adobe.com/products/firefly.html\">Adobe Firefly</a> suggests options and sliders to adjust the outcome. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/7-adobe-firefly.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>Refinement is usually <strong>the most painful part of the experience</strong>, with many fine details being left to users to explain elaborately. But we can use good old-fashioned UI controls like knobs, sliders, buttons, and so on to improve that experience, similar to how Adobe Firefly does it (image above).</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://maggieappleton.com/lm-sketchbook/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/fc5bc01c-8439-4454-b87b-289942133000/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0c31b829-d8af-4a6b-9a9c-464077be0100/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3ea85625-d579-40c1-092b-c3f651da6f00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/65785302-a4cd-4cb1-0f41-a4a85175fd00/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b1f05077-d94b-448d-7344-a8eb8b0a1b00/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/fc5bc01c-8439-4454-b87b-289942133000/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Presets living on the side in Elicit, an <a href=\"https://maggieappleton.com/lm-sketchbook/\">example</a> by Maggie Appleton. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/8-illustration-output-ux.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>We can also use presets, bookmarks, and allow users to <strong>highlight specific parts of the outcome</strong> that they’d like to change — with contextual prompts acting on highlighted parts of the output, rather than global prompts.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://www.grammarly.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/553ae5e3-6945-41b0-1a3f-01cae2cc5500/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7c592319-3c7c-409f-b797-ae00830a6800/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/10c928bf-6909-484a-499c-f1a5b23c2900/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/aaba6d2e-bd58-4259-4b25-43dadb7b3600/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/56a60451-341e-4bb4-ce8e-9ba09448cc00/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/553ae5e3-6945-41b0-1a3f-01cae2cc5500/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Tweaking specific parts of the outcome, on <a href=\"https://www.grammarly.com/\">Grammarly</a>. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/9-illustration-output-ux.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <h2 id=\"ai-actions-tasks-to-complete\">AI Actions: Tasks To Complete</h2>\n   <p>With AI agents, we can now also <strong>allow users to initiate tasks</strong> that AI can perform on their behalf, such as scheduling events, planning, and deep research. We could also ask to <strong>sort results or filter them</strong> in a specific way.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://maggieappleton.com/lm-sketchbook/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"469\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4378726b-4867-4909-dbbf-f7dbe2079c00/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/53ebecf2-17b3-4fd4-f33b-7d10fd50a300/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2cbf4e66-7996-40b9-dfac-aa1baa13e700/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9beebf87-d469-4bb2-4dc1-7e25307fdf00/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/8a440359-967d-4398-53ed-66bd53d88600/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4378726b-4867-4909-dbbf-f7dbe2079c00/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of Output UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Suggesting actions on Elicit, an <a href=\"https://maggieappleton.com/lm-sketchbook/\">example</a> by Maggie Appleton. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/10-illustration-output-ux.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>But we can also add features to help users use AI output better — e.g., by visualizing it, making it shareable, allowing <strong>transformations</strong> between formats, or also posting to Slack, Jira, and so on.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"ai-integration-where-work-happens\">AI Integration: Where Work Happens</h2>\n   <p>Many AI interactions are locked within a specific product, but good AI experiences happen <strong>where the actual work happens</strong>. It would be quite unusual to expect a dedicated section for <em>Autocomplete</em>, for example, but we do so for AI features.</p>\n   <figure class=\"break-out article__image\">\n    <a href=\"https://dovetail.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4ce9f588-29cc-4361-05ff-47b964741400/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4168c4a5-89bd-4501-92e8-7511ed040800/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f08518e8-0471-4432-1b94-76b4f3d31800/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0ce76bb4-837b-4202-6d81-83cf0103e600/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4d85ce4b-7fd0-4c80-c0ce-e5650e6fd500/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/4ce9f588-29cc-4361-05ff-47b964741400/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of AI Integration UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/11-illustration-ai-integration-ux.png\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <figure>\n    <a href=\"https://dovetail.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"800\" height=\"823\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/68da4457-3568-4bbb-f495-68eaa878ef00/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0753e39f-4776-48fb-1704-9960ee3a9500/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/118afda5-d899-4d90-e0c2-2fa1210fea00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f2051b85-7852-421c-bd96-80f3edede000/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ff5fda29-7ece-440e-5ea9-69581d433300/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/68da4457-3568-4bbb-f495-68eaa878ef00/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Illustration of AI Integration UX\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     <a href=\"https://dovetail.com/\">DoveTail AI</a> integrates in plenty of platforms, from Jira and Notion to Slack and Teams, where the actual work happens. (<a href=\"https://files.smashing.media/articles/design-patterns-ai-interfaces/12-dovetail.jpg\">Large preview</a>)\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <p>The actual boost in productivity comes when users rely on AI as a co-pilot or little helper in the <strong>tools they use daily for work</strong>. It’s seamless integrations into Slack, Teams, Jira, GitHub, and so on — the tools that people use anyway. <a href=\"https://www.diabrowser.com/\">Dia Browser</a> and <a href=\"https://dovetail.com/\">Dovetail</a> are great examples of it in action.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"wrapping-up\">Wrapping Up</h2>\n   <p>Along these five areas, we can explore ways to <strong>minimize the cost of interaction</strong> with a textbox, and allow users to interact with the points of interest directly, by tapping, clicking, selecting, highlighting, and bookmarking.</p>\n   <p>Many products are obsessed with being AI-first. But you might be way better off by being <strong>AI-second</strong> instead. The difference is that we focus on user needs and sprinkle a bit of AI across customer journeys where it actually adds value.</p>\n   <p>And AI products don’t have to be AI-only. There is a lot of value in mapping into the mental models that people have adopted over the years, and <strong>enhance them with AI</strong>, similar to how we do it with browsers’ autofill, rather than leaving users in front of a frightening and omnipresent text box.</p>\n   <h2 id=\"useful-resources\">Useful Resources</h2>\n   <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"https://uxdesign.cc/where-should-ai-sit-in-your-ui-1710a258390e\">Where Should AI Sit In Your UI?</a>, by Sharang Sharma</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://shapeof.ai/\">Shape of AI: Design Patterns</a>, by Emily Campbell</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://www.aiuxpatterns.com/\">AI UX Patterns</a>, by Luke Bennis</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://catalogue.projectsbyif.com/\">Design Patterns For Trust With AI</a>, via Sarah Gold</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://pair.withgoogle.com/guidebook/patterns\">AI Guidebook Design Patterns</a>, by Google</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2093\">Usable Chat Interfaces to AI Models</a>, by Luke Wroblewski</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2105\">The Receding Role of AI Chat</a>, by Luke Wroblewski</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?2106\">Agent Management Interface Patterns</a>, by Luke Wroblewski</li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://uxdesign.cc/designing-for-ai-engineers-what-ui-patterns-and-principles-you-need-to-know-8b16a5b62a61\">Designing for AI Engineers</a>, by Eve Weinberg</li>\n   </ul>\n   <h2 id=\"meet-smart-interface-design-patterns\">Meet “Smart Interface Design Patterns”</h2>\n   <p>You can find more details on <strong>design patterns and UX</strong> in <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/\"><strong>Smart Interface Design Patterns</strong></a>, our <strong>15h-video course</strong> with 100s of practical examples from real-life projects — with a live UX training later this year. Everything from mega-dropdowns to complex enterprise tables — with 5 new segments added every year. <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jhZ3el3n-u0\">Jump to a free preview</a>. Use code <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com\"><strong>BIRDIE</strong></a> to <strong>save 15%</strong> off.</p>\n   <figure style=\"margin-bottom:0\">\n    <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/\"><img style=\"border-radius:11px\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" width=\"950\" height=\"492\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/937b9568-ccf4-45ea-6329-32bca457de00/public 400w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/95ef801a-5fb3-4c4c-0257-161a46546a00/public 800w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/cdb20a72-3022-4f7f-1b4e-a837f758ef00/public 1200w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/2dd3d4db-0f77-469d-875d-996fd72adb00/public 1600w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d037cc0f-8ae9-47d8-0885-527f8a040e00/public 2000w\" src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/937b9568-ccf4-45ea-6329-32bca457de00/public\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Smart Interface Design Patterns\"></a>\n    <figcaption class=\"op-vertical-bottom\">\n     Meet <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.com/\">Smart Interface Design Patterns</a>, our video course on interface design &amp; UX.\n    </figcaption>\n   </figure>\n   <div class=\"book-cta__inverted\">\n    <div class=\"book-cta\" data-handler=\"ContentTabs\" data-mq=\"(max-width: 480px)\">\n     <nav class=\"content-tabs content-tabs--books\">\n      <ul>\n       <li class=\"content-tab\"><a href=\"#\">\n         <button class=\"btn btn--small btn--white btn--white--bordered\">Video + UX Training</button></a></li>\n       <li class=\"content-tab\"><a href=\"#\">\n         <button class=\"btn btn--small btn--white btn--white--bordered\">Video only</button></a></li>\n      </ul>\n     </nav>\n     <div class=\"book-cta__col book-cta__hardcover content-tab--content\">\n      <h3 class=\"book-cta__title\"><span>Video + UX Training</span></h3><span class=\"book-cta__price\"><span><span><span class=\"currency-sign\">$</span>&nbsp;<span>495<span class=\"sup\">.00</span></span></span> <span class=\"book-cta__price--old\"><span class=\"currency-sign\">$</span>&nbsp;<span>699<span class=\"sup\">.00</span></span></span></span></span> <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.thinkific.com/enroll/3081832?price_id=3951439\" class=\"btn btn--full btn--medium btn--text-shadow\">Get Video + UX Training</a>\n      <p class=\"book-cta__desc\">25 video lessons (15h) + <a href=\"https://smashingconf.com/online-workshops/workshops/vitaly-friedman-impact-design/\">Live UX Training</a>.<br>\n        100 days money-back-guarantee.</p>\n     </div>\n     <div class=\"book-cta__col book-cta__ebook content-tab--content\">\n      <h3 class=\"book-cta__title\"><span>Video only</span></h3>\n      <div data-audience=\"anonymous free supporter\" data-remove=\"true\">\n       <span class=\"book-cta__price\" data-handler=\"PriceTag\"><span><span><span class=\"currency-sign\">$</span>&nbsp;<span>300<span class=\"sup\">.00</span></span></span><span class=\"book-cta__price--old\"><span class=\"currency-sign\">$</span>&nbsp;<span>395<span class=\"sup\">.00</span></span></span></span></span>\n      </div><a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.thinkific.com/enroll/3081832?price_id=3950630\" class=\"btn btn--full btn--medium btn--text-shadow\">Get the video course</a>\n      <p class=\"book-cta__desc\" data-audience=\"anonymous free supporter\" data-remove=\"true\">40 video lessons (15h). Updated yearly.<br>\n        Also available as a <a href=\"https://smart-interface-design-patterns.thinkific.com/enroll/3082557?price_id=3951421\">UX Bundle with 2 video courses.</a></p>\n     </div><span></span>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文概述了一种设计有效 AI 界面的系统方法，提倡从以聊天为中心转向以任务为导向的 UI，重点关注优化输入、输出、改进流程、操作和无缝集成。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文概述了一种设计有效 AI 界面的系统方法，提倡从以聊天为中心转向以任务为导向的 UI，重点关注优化输入、输出、改进流程、操作和无缝集成。",
  "summary": "本文提供了一个全面的指南，用于设计超越传统对话界面的 AI 用户体验。它强调了一个重要的行业转变，即 AI 的角色正变得更具组织性和任务导向性，而不是纯粹基于聊天。作者确定了五个关键领域来塑造更好的 AI 体验：通过视觉和 AI 辅助工具最大限度地减少手动提示输入来优化输入；增强输出显示，以提供由洞察驱动的可视化，而不仅仅是纯文本；使用熟悉的 UI 控件简化优化流程；使 AI 代理能够代表用户执行可操作的任务；以及将 AI 无缝集成到现有的日常工作工具中。核心理念提倡“后 AI”方法，即 AI 谨慎地增强用户工作流程并在上下文中增加价值，同时最大限度地降低用户与 AI 功能交互的总体成本，避免用户面对专用且可能复杂、难以理解的独立界面。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "AI 界面设计正在从以聊天为中心转向以任务为中心的 UI。",
      "explanation": "传统的聊天界面通常效率低下，无法表达用户意图，因此需要专注于以任务为中心的组件、预设和模板，这些组件、预设和模板强调结果而不是冗长的对话输入。"
    },
    {
      "point": "优化 AI 输入和输出 UX 对于用户效率和洞察力至关重要。",
      "explanation": "通过可视化工具或 AI 生成的提示来最大限度地减少手动提示输入，以及将 AI 输出以可视化形式呈现，而不仅仅是纯文本，可以显著提高可用性并帮助用户更快地获得洞察力。"
    },
    {
      "point": "将 AI 无缝集成到日常工作流程中可以最大限度地提高生产力和价值。",
      "explanation": "将 AI 作为助手直接集成到用户现有的工作工具（例如，Slack、Jira）中，而不是独立的 AI 功能，可以提供更自然和高效的体验。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "消息 UI 慢慢开始感觉过时，聊天 UI 逐渐消失在背景中。",
    "事实上，聊天机器人很少是一种很棒的体验范例——主要是因为有效表达意图的负担在于用户。",
    "为了设计更好的 AI 体验，我们需要研究我们需要塑造的 5 个关键领域。",
    "总而言之，我们可以最大限度地减少手动输入提示的负担——通过 AI 生成的预提示、提示扩展、查询构建器以及语音输入。",
    "许多产品都痴迷于成为 AI 优先，但你最好是“后 AI”。"
  ],
